    <h2>About Me</h2>
    <p>
      I am a researcher passionate about understanding how digital consumers build trust, perceive risk, and make decisions in online environments.
      My research integrates emotional and cognitive perspectives on marketing psychology, focusing on emerging markets such as Iran.
    </p>
    <p>
      Over the past decade, I have worked in marketing and sales management within the health and beauty industries, leading promotional campaigns and developing data-driven consumer insights.
      My academic goal is to pursue doctoral research that contributes to global understanding of consumer behaviour and digital marketing ethics.
    </p>
